 STRUCTURE:
1.ﻗ·  ﻗ· Introduction
Importance of customer feedback
Objective of analysis
2.ﻗ·  ﻗ· Problem Statement
Identify satisfaction drivers
Detect underperforming products
3.ﻗ·  ﻗ· Data Cleaning
Handled missing values
Removed duplicates
Converted timestamps
Created sentiment & review length features
4.ﻗ·  ﻗ· Exploratory Data Analysis
Rating distribution shows majority positive reviews
Product-level analysis reveals top and worst performers
Verified users provide more consistent ratings
Negative reviews are longer and more detailed
5.ﻗ·  ﻗ· Statistical Analysis
Correlation between variables is weak
T-test conducted on verified vs non-verified ratings
Interpretation based on p-value
6.ﻗ·  ﻗ· Dashboard Overview
Interactive Tableau dashboard
Filters for product and sentiment
Visual insights into customer behavior
7.ﻗ·  ﻗ· Key Insights
Product quality issues drive negative sentiment
Verified reviews are more reliable
Customer dissatisfaction is concentrated in specific products
8.ﻗ·  ﻗ· Recommendations
Improve low-rated products
Address recurring negative feedback
Focus on verified customer insights
Enhance product descriptions
9.ﻗ·  ﻗ· Conclusion
Data-driven insights can significantly improve customer satisfaction and product performance
